reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fine cables, good price.
reviews.reviewText: I bought these USB C to USB A cables to replace the package of the same I bought a while back and now can't find. We don't have a lot of USB C devices, just our two cell phones. But it appears that USB C is here to stay, and eventually we will have other things besides our phones that use the interface. These are well made cables, and were selected not just by price, but also for the variety of lengths and the cloth covers. They work well and should last us a long time.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 14, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Value and Quality Charging Cables!
reviews.reviewText: I recently purchased the 5Pack (3/3/6/6/10FT) Fast Charging USB-C to USB-A Cable set in blue, and I must say, I am thoroughly impressed with the quality and performance of these cables.First and foremost, the variety of cable lengths in this pack is incredibly convenient. Whether I need a short 3-foot cable for charging my phone on my desk or a longer 10-foot cable for using my device while it charges from across the room, this set has it all.The cables are also labeled clearly with their respective lengths, which is a nice touch for organization.When it comes to charging speed, these cables deliver as promised. The 3A fast charging capability ensures that my Samsung Galaxy S10 charges quickly and efficiently, which is crucial for my busy lifestyle.I've also tested them with other devices like my LG V50, and they perform admirably with a range of gadgets.Durability is another highlight of these cables. The braided design not only adds to their aesthetic appeal but also provides robust protection against wear and tear.I've bent and twisted these cables numerous times, and they show no signs of fraying or damage.The compatibility of these cables with various devices, including Samsung Galaxy phones and LG models, is a significant plus. I no longer need to hunt for specific cables for different devices; this set covers all my needs.In conclusion, the 5Pack Fast Charging USB-C to USB-A Cable set is an excellent purchase.It offers a variety of cable lengths, fast charging capabilities, durability, and compatibility at an affordable price.I highly recommend these cables to anyone in need of reliable charging solutions for their devices.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These things are great
reviews.reviewText: Review for "5Pack (3/3/6/6/10FT) Fast Charging 3A USB-C to USB-A Cable Rapid Charger Quick Cord Comp..."Not all USB cables are created equal, and it's easy to spend too much money on cables that look decent or make big claims that end up not working well or breaking. Especially in most stores. ESPECIALLY convenience stores. I see so many people spend upwards of $15 for a single cable that ends up being junk. I've done it myself. Live and learn. I work retail and worked many years in convenience stores, and I've sold many USB cables to unsuspecting victims, though I did try to warn people.For the price (or even a higher price), these cables work great and they last. And, if you've run into this issue before like I did, they both charge and transfer data. Before I bought these I was going through all of the various cheapie and free cables I'd gotten over the years so I could transfer data between my phone and computer, and only one of them transferred data. The rest would only charge. I didn't know that was a thing. I just thought a USB cable did what USB cables were supposed to do. So I'm pleased. I have multiples of several different lengths so I can keep cables in various places and not have to search for one, and they do what I've always thought USB cables are supposed to do. All for a crazy-good price. I'm set for now, but if I need to buy more, these are the ones I'm looking for. If you think you might need a USB cable soon, order these before you end up at a convenience store with a dead phone and have to spend way too much money on junk so you can get back in action again.
